page.title: 17SURVEY OF WOODFORD TREES
page.content: We drove about the Woodford Valley looking for trees. We counted 68 Oak trees , we found out that the Oaks went in rows and once they started they went on for quite a while. The Sycamore scattered itself hither and thither all over the country side. We noticed 71 Sycamore trees as this is an area with many of them. We didn't notice many Beeches, but even fewer Horse Chestnuts, 40 Beeches & 13 Horse Chestnuts. A large and sturdy figure of a Plane tree was only seen twice. Willows scattered themselves by the river,we saw 82 and also 63 Ash. Limes were not common & there were only 10. We only saw 27 Elder trees which surprised me because in the Autumn the area was full of Elder berries on Elder trees. We were astounded to see elms which were alive, and we counted 65 of them.
